==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exhortation
<hw>Ex`hor*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exhortatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>exhortation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of practice of exhorting; the act of inciting to laudable
deeds; incitement to that which is good or commendable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Language intended to incite and encourage; advice;
counsel; admonition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll end my <qex>exhortation</qex> after dinner.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 525 --></p>

<p><ent>Exhortative</ent>⟦br⟧
